The operating rod is marked "D 35382-0" on the top and does have the modified cutout, the recoil spring is an original style square edge "Keystone" spring, and it has a correct style square comp spring.  The bolt is marked "D 28287-1 J6". The trigger housing is numbered "D 28290" without pad, small hole, hammer number "C 46008-1" (on the side) with hole, safety "C-46015-4", parkerized hammer spring housing, trigger guard "C 46025" with rings. The rear sight assembly is marked "B-8868-1" on the rear sight aperture, "B8872" on the sight cover. Knob marked "LEFT" and "RIGHT" with flared arrows. The elevation is marked "UP" and "DOWN " and "BATTLE RANGE" with the pointer triangle, closed arrows. Front stock/sling swivel band marked “C46013-1”.  The middle band is grooved and notched at the bottom (C-46000-0), the rear hand guard clip is grooved, the milled bullet guide is marked "B-8875", and the follower arm is marked "B8869" with 2 bevels. The follower and clip latch are both unnumbered. The stock is marked with a circled "P" proof on the pistol grip and “S.A. S.P.G” in a box on the left.  The butt area has 2 unequal holes (one large, one small) has been modified under the buttplate for cleaning kit and the buttplate is un- numbered and has no door.  (Screws not numbered.) The receiver marked “D 28291” on left front under stock.   We were told by the seller this rifle was restored but Scott Duff.

title: For Sale:  O-PAP M70 YUGO - BRAND NEW AK-47 W/ CREST BEST AK AK47 ZASTAVA
postcontent:
Up got sale is a CAI Zastava O-PAP rifle. For those of you that are not familiar, this is an extremely rare find, of one of the, if not the, best AK47 to be imported in the last 20 years. These are comparable to the Mitchell Arm's Yugo AK's from the early 90's. Those guns are now extremely collectible and much more valuable that this relative bargain that this gun is. 

These rifles were built out of de-milled machine guns. Century Arms International had found a cache of the guns and then sent them to Zastava to have them rebuild on semi-automatic receivers. These were a limited production run and made out of actual military rifles that had been sitting around for decades! Some of the parts show their age, such as the wood, due to being military storage for so long. The production has been ended for quite some time now and these are no longer available for sale. 

Even rarer is that this particular gun has a Serbian crest engraved into the buttstock. Only a small amount had received this very interesting additional. No one seems to know many many got it, but it seems to only have been a small amount, produced early on in the production run. These are considered more desirable to collectors.

This is a spare one that I had bought and it is still NEW in the box. I only took it out to take pictures. The gun is complete with accessories and has never been used. The gun is nice and straight and is one of the nicest I have seen. It was hand picked by me. I was planning on holding onto this one, but decided I have to slim my collection down. My loss is your gain! Do not miss your chance to own a piece of history!

I have a Springfield Range Officer with a 460 Rowland barrel installed for those that do not know about the 460 Rowland it makes a 45acp into a handgun as powerful as a 44 Mag. I purchased this with the intention of hunting with it but F&G tells me that it is not one of the accepted cartridges for handgun hunting in NH. 

It comes complete ready to shoot I have a few handloads for it and 100 rounds of unloaded 460 Rowland brass I will include load data. Out of the 460 Rowland barrel you can shoot 45acp, 45 super or 460 Rowland. It also comes with the complete Springfield Box (holster mag holder paperwork and 2 Mags. 

I also have the complete Range Officer barrel set up which is included. 

Factory 460 Rowland ammo is available through many online sources like Midway.

You can not shoot 460 Rowland brass in a normal 45acp barrel the brass is 1/16th longer then a 45acp case you do use 45 acp dies to load the 460 Rowland

Check out 460Rowland.com for more info on this load.
